<xref type="reprint from" targOrder="U" from="ROOT" to="DITTO" n="sb;4;7353" evaluate="all">SB4,7353</xref></head><div type="edition" lang="grc" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><div type="textpart" n="r" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="1"/>Ἀπολινᾶρις <choice><corr>Ταήσει</corr><sic>ταησι</sic></choice> τῇ <choice><corr>μητρὶ</corr><sic>μητρει</sic></choice> καὶ κυρίᾳ 

    <lb n="2"/>πολλὰ χαίρειν. πρὸ μὲν πάντων εὔχομαί σε 

    <lb n="3"/><choice><corr>ὑγιαίνειν</corr><sic><hi rend="diaeresis">υ</hi>γειαινειν</sic></choice> <choice><corr>καὶ ἐγὼ</corr><sic>καγω</sic></choice> αὐτὸς <choice><corr>ὑγιαίνω</corr><sic><hi rend="diaeresis">υ</hi>γειαινω</sic></choice> καὶ τὸ προσκύνη-

    <lb n="4"/>μά σου ποιῶ παρὰ τοῖς ἐνθάδε θεοῖς. <choice><corr>γινώσκειν</corr><sic>γεινωσκειν</sic></choice> σε 

    <lb n="5"/>θέλω, μήτηρ, ὅτι ἐρρωμένος ἐγενόμην εἰς Ῥώμην 

    <lb n="6"/>Παχὼν μηνὶ <num value="25">κε</num> καὶ ἐκληρώθην εἰς Μισηνούς. 

    <lb n="7"/>οὔπω δὲ τὴν <choice><corr>κε<supplied reason="omitted" cert="high">ν</supplied>τυρίαν</corr><sic>κετυριαν</sic></choice> μου ἔγνων· οὐ γὰρ <choice><corr>ἀπε-

    <lb n="8"/>ληλύθειν</corr><sic>απεληλυτειν</sic></choice> εἰς Μισηνοὺς ὅτε σοι τὴν ἐπιστολὴν ταύτην 

    <lb n="9"/>ἔγραφον. ἐρωτῶ σε οὖν, μήτηρ, σεαυτῇ πρόσεχε, 

    <lb n="10"/>μηδὲν δίσταζε περὶ ἐμοῦ· ἐγὼ γὰρ εἰς καλὸν τό-

    <lb n="11"/>πον ἦλθον. καλῶς δὲ <choice><corr>ποιήσ<supplied reason="omitted" cert="high">εις</supplied></corr><sic>ποιης</sic></choice> <choice><corr>γράψασά</corr><sic>γραψασσα</sic></choice> μοι ἐπιστο-

    <lb n="12"/>λὴν πε<supplied reason="lost" cert="high">ρ</supplied>ὶ τῆς σωτηρίας σου καὶ τῶν ἀδελφῶν μου καὶ 

    <lb n="13"/>τῶν σῶν πάντων. καὶ <choice><corr>ἐγὼ</corr><sic>γω</sic></choice> εἴ τινα ἐὰν εὕρω γράφω 

    <lb n="14"/>σοι· οὐ μὴ ὀκνήσω σοι <choice><corr>γράφειν</corr><sic>γραφιν</sic></choice>. ἀσπάζομαι τοὺς ἀ-

    <lb n="15"/>δελφούς μου πολλὰ καὶ Ἀπολινᾶριν καὶ τὰ τέ-

    <lb n="16"/>κνα αὐτοῦ καὶ Καραλᾶν καὶ τὰ τέκνα αὐτοῦ. 

    <lb n="17"/>ἀσπάζ<supplied reason="lost" cert="high">ο</supplied>μαι Πτολεμαῖν καὶ Πτολεμαείδα καὶ τὰ 

    <lb n="18"/>τέκν<supplied reason="lost" cert="high">α</supplied> αὐτῆς καὶ Ἡρακλοῦν καὶ τὰ τέκνα αὐτῆς. 

    <lb n="19"/>ἀσπάζομαι τοὺς φιλοῦντάς σε πάντας κατ᾽ ὄνο-

    <lb n="20"/>μα. 

    <lb n="21"/>ἐρρῶσθαί σε εὔχομαι. 
</ab></div><div type="textpart" n="v" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="22"/><expan>ἀπόδ<ex cert="high">ος</ex></expan> εἰς Καρανίδα <g type="x"/> <choice><corr>Ταήσει</corr><sic>ταησι</sic></choice> ἀπὸ Ἀπολιναρίου <choice><corr>υἱοῦ</corr><sic>υειου</sic></choice> 

    <lb n="23"/><g type="x"/> Μισηνάτου. </ab></div></div><div n="meta.27101" type="description" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p><rs type="material" cert="high">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.27101" type="commentary" subtype="textDate" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p><date type="textDate" notBefore="101" notAfter="200">II</date></p></div><div n="meta.27101" type="commentary" subtype="mentionedDates" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><head>Erwähnte Daten</head></div><div n="meta.27101" type="bibliography" subtype="principalEdition" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><listBibl default="NO"><bibl type="publication" subtype="principal" default="NO"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Mich.</title><biblScope type="volume">8</biblScope><biblScope type="numbers">491</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="Trismegistos" default="NO"><biblScope type="numbers">27101</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="DDbDP" default="NO"><series>0163</series>; <biblScope type="volume">8</biblScope>; <biblScope type="numbers">491</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref type="Perseus" href="0163;8;491" evaluate="all" from="ROOT" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.27101" type="bibliography" subtype="illustrations" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p><bibl type="illustration" default="NO">Class. Phil. 22, 1927, Plate II nach S. 242</bibl><bibl type="illustration" default="NO">White, Ancient Letters, S. 163</bibl></p></div><div n="meta.27101" type="bibliography" subtype="otherPublications" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><head>Andere Publikationen</head><listBibl default="NO"><bibl type="publication" subtype="other" default="NO">SB IV 7353</bibl><bibl type="publication" subtype="other" default="NO">Sel. Pap. I 111</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.27101" type="bibliography" subtype="translations" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><head>Übersetzungen</head><listBibl lang="de" default="NO"><head lang